A triple-bill of silent films, featuring Laurel and Hardy, Nazimova and Catherine Hessling, is to be shown on Dec. 9 at 7 and 9 P.M. at the Cathedral of St. John the Divine, Amsterdam Avenue at 112th Street. The films are ''Big Business'' (1929) with Laurel and Hardy; ''Salome'' (1922) with Nazimova, and ''The Little Match Girl'' (1928), directed by Jean Renoir and featuring Catherine Hessling. Piano music, composed and performed by Lee Erwin, is to be featured at the screenings. Tickets are $5. Information: 662-2133.